{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Gen|35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","chapter":35,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":1,"text":"God said to Jacob, “Get up! Go to Bethel and settle there. Build an altar there to the God who appeared to you when you fled from your brother Esau.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":2,"text":"So Jacob said to his family and all who were with him, “Get rid of the foreign gods that are among you. Purify yourselves and change your clothes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":3,"text":"We must get up and go to Bethel. I will build an altar there to the God who answered me in my day of distress. He has been with me everywhere I have gone.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":4,"text":"Then they gave Jacob all their foreign gods and their earrings, and Jacob hid them under the oak near Shechem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":5,"text":"When they set out, a terror from God came over the cities around them, and they did not pursue Jacob’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":6,"text":"So Jacob and all who were with him came to Luz (that is, Bethel ) in the land of Canaan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":7,"text":"Jacob built an altar there and called the place El-bethel because it was there that God had revealed himself to him when he was fleeing from his brother.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":8,"text":"Deborah, the one who had nursed and raised Rebekah, died and was buried under the oak south of Bethel. So Jacob named it Allon-bacuth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":9,"text":"God appeared to Jacob again after he returned from Paddan-aram, and he blessed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":10,"text":"God said to him, “Your name is Jacob; you will no longer be named Jacob, but your name will be Israel.” So he named him Israel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":11,"text":"God also said to him, “I am God Almighty. Be fruitful and multiply. A nation, indeed an assembly of nations, will come from you, and kings will descend from you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":12,"text":"I will give to you the land that I gave to Abraham and Isaac. And I will give the land to your future descendants.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":13,"text":"Then God withdrew from him at the place where he had spoken to him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":14,"text":"Jacob set up a marker at the place where he had spoken to him —a stone marker. He poured a drink offering on it and poured oil on it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":15,"text":"Jacob named the place where God had spoken with him Bethel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":16,"text":"They set out from Bethel. When they were still some distance from Ephrath, Rachel began to give birth, and her labor was difficult.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":17,"text":"During her difficult labor, the midwife said to her, “Don’t be afraid, for you have another son.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":18,"text":"With her last breath —for she was dying —she named him Ben-oni, but his father called him Benjamin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":19,"text":"So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem ).","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":20,"text":"Jacob set up a marker on her grave; it is the marker at Rachel’s grave still today.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":21,"text":"Israel set out again and pitched his tent beyond the Tower of Eder.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":22,"text":"While Israel was living in that region, Reuben went in and slept with his father’s concubine Bilhah, and Israel heard about it. Jacob had twelve sons:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":23,"text":"Leah’s sons were Reuben (Jacob’s firstborn), Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":24,"text":"Rachel’s sons were Joseph and Benjamin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":25,"text":"The sons of Rachel’s slave Bilhah were Dan and Naphtali.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":26,"text":"The sons of Leah’s slave Zilpah were Gad and Asher. These are the sons of Jacob, who were born to him in Paddan-aram.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":27,"text":"Jacob came to his father Isaac at Mamre in Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron ), where Abraham and Isaac had stayed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":28,"text":"Isaac lived 180 years.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","bookOrder":0,"chapter":35,"verse":29,"text":"He took his last breath and died, and was gathered to his people, old and full of days. His sons Esau and Jacob buried him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gen","chapter":35,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,4,8,9,14,16,21,23,24,25,26,27],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Return to Bethel"},{"beforeVerse":16,"text":"Rachel’s Death"},{"beforeVerse":21,"text":"Israel’s Sons"},{"beforeVerse":27,"text":"Isaac’s Death"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God said to Jacob, “Get up! Go to Bethel and settle there. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Build an altar there to the God who appeared to you when you fled from your brother Esau.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 27:43","book":"Gen","chapter":27,"verse":43,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 28:19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":19},{"label":"Gn 27:43","book":"Gen","chapter":27,"verse":43}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Jacob said to his family and all who were with him, “Get rid of the foreign gods that are among you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 31:19","book":"Gen","chapter":31,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 24:23","book":"Jos","chapter":24,"verse":23,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 7:3","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Purify yourselves and change your clothes. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 19:10","book":"Exo","chapter":19,"verse":10,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 31:19","book":"Gen","chapter":31,"verse":19},{"label":"Jos 24:23","book":"Jos","chapter":24,"verse":23},{"label":"1Sm 7:3","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":3},{"label":"Ex 19:10","book":"Exo","chapter":19,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"We must get up and go to Bethel. I will build an altar there to the God who answered me in my day of distress. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 7:9","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 24:25","book":"2Sa","chapter":24,"verse":25,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jb 12:4","book":"Job","chapter":12,"verse":4,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 20:1","book":"Psa","chapter":20,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 34:4","book":"Psa","chapter":34,"verse":4,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" He has been with me everywhere I have gone.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:10–22","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":10,"letter":"f"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 7:9","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":9},{"label":"2Sm 24:25","book":"2Sa","chapter":24,"verse":25},{"label":"Jb 12:4","book":"Job","chapter":12,"verse":4},{"label":"Ps 20:1","book":"Psa","chapter":20,"verse":1},{"label":"Ps 34:4","book":"Psa","chapter":34,"verse":4},{"label":"Gn 28:10–22","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then they gave Jacob all their foreign gods and their earrings, and Jacob hid them under the oak near Shechem. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When they set out, a terror from God came over the cities around them, and they did not pursue Jacob’s sons. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 23:27","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 23:27","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Jacob and all who were with him came to Luz (that is, Bethel "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 48:3","book":"Gen","chapter":48,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":") in the land of Canaan. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 28:19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":19},{"label":"Gn 48:3","book":"Gen","chapter":48,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jacob built an altar there and called the place El-bethel "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"= God of Bethel"},{"kind":"text","text":" because it was there that God had revealed himself to him when he was fleeing from his brother."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"= God of Bethel"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Deborah, the one who had nursed and raised Rebekah, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit Deborah, Rebekah’s wet nurse; Gn 24:59"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 24:59","book":"Gen","chapter":24,"verse":59,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" died and was buried under the oak south of Bethel. So Jacob named it Allon-bacuth. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"= Oak of Weeping"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 24:59","book":"Gen","chapter":24,"verse":59}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit Deborah, Rebekah’s wet nurse; Gn 24:59"},{"marker":2,"text":"= Oak of Weeping"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God appeared to Jacob again after he returned from Paddan-aram, and he blessed him. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God said to him, “Your name is Jacob; you will no longer be named Jacob, but your name will be Israel.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 17:5","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 32:28","book":"Gen","chapter":32,"verse":28,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" So he named him Israel. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 17:5","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":5},{"label":"Gn 32:28","book":"Gen","chapter":32,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God also said to him, “I am God Almighty. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 17:1","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:3","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 6:3","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Be fruitful and multiply. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 9:1","book":"Gen","chapter":9,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 9:7","book":"Gen","chapter":9,"verse":7,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" A nation, indeed an assembly of nations, will come from you, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 48:4","book":"Gen","chapter":48,"verse":4,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" and kings will descend from you. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit will come from your loins"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 17:6","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":6,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 17:16","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":16,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:31","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":31,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 17:1","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":1},{"label":"Gn 28:3","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":3},{"label":"Ex 6:3","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":3},{"label":"Gn 9:1","book":"Gen","chapter":9,"verse":1},{"label":"Gn 9:7","book":"Gen","chapter":9,"verse":7},{"label":"Gn 48:4","book":"Gen","chapter":48,"verse":4},{"label":"Gn 17:6","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":6},{"label":"Gn 17:16","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":16},{"label":"Gn 36:31","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":31}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit will come from your loins"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will give to you the land that I gave to Abraham and Isaac. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 12:7","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 13:15","book":"Gen","chapter":13,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 26:3–4","book":"Gen","chapter":26,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:13","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":13,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:13","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":13,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" And I will give the land to your future descendants.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 12:7","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":7},{"label":"Gn 13:15","book":"Gen","chapter":13,"verse":15},{"label":"Gn 26:3–4","book":"Gen","chapter":26,"verse":3},{"label":"Gn 28:13","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":13},{"label":"Ex 32:13","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then God withdrew "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit went up"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 17:22","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 18:33","book":"Gen","chapter":18,"verse":33,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" from him at the place where he had spoken to him."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 17:22","book":"Gen","chapter":17,"verse":22},{"label":"Gn 18:33","book":"Gen","chapter":18,"verse":33}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Lit went up"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jacob set up a marker at the place where he had spoken to him —a stone marker. He poured a drink offering on it and poured oil on it. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 28:18–19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 31:45","book":"Gen","chapter":31,"verse":45,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 28:18–19","book":"Gen","chapter":28,"verse":18},{"label":"Gn 31:45","book":"Gen","chapter":31,"verse":45}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jacob named the place where God had spoken with him Bethel."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They set out from Bethel. When they were still some distance from Ephrath, Rachel began to give birth, and her labor was difficult. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"During her difficult labor, the midwife said to her, “Don’t be afraid, for you have another son.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 30:24","book":"Gen","chapter":30,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 30:24","book":"Gen","chapter":30,"verse":24}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"With her last breath —for she was dying —she named him Ben-oni, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"= Son of My Sorrow"},{"kind":"text","text":" but his father called him Benjamin. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"= Son of the Right Hand"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"= Son of My Sorrow"},{"marker":2,"text":"= Son of the Right Hand"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mc 5:2","book":"Mic","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 2:18","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":"). "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mc 5:2","book":"Mic","chapter":5,"verse":2},{"label":"Mt 2:18","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jacob set up a marker on her grave; it is the marker at Rachel’s grave still today."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Israel set out again and pitched his tent beyond the Tower of Eder. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or beyond Migdal-eder"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or beyond Migdal-eder"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"While Israel was living in that region, Reuben went in and slept with his father’s concubine Bilhah, and Israel heard about it. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 49:3–4","book":"Gen","chapter":49,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Jacob had twelve sons: "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 2:1–2","book":"1Ch","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 49:3–4","book":"Gen","chapter":49,"verse":3},{"label":"1Ch 2:1–2","book":"1Ch","chapter":2,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Leah’s sons were Reuben (Jacob’s firstborn),"},{"kind":"text","text":" Simeon, Levi, Judah,"},{"kind":"text","text":" Issachar, and Zebulun."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Rachel’s sons were"},{"kind":"text","text":" Joseph and Benjamin."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The sons of Rachel’s slave Bilhah"},{"kind":"text","text":" were Dan and Naphtali."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The sons of Leah’s slave Zilpah"},{"kind":"text","text":" were Gad and Asher."},{"kind":"text","text":" These are the sons of Jacob, who were born to him in Paddan-aram."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jacob came to his father Isaac at Mamre "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 13:18","book":"Gen","chapter":13,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 18:1","book":"Gen","chapter":18,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 23:19","book":"Gen","chapter":23,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" in Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 14:15","book":"Jos","chapter":14,"verse":15,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":"), where Abraham and Isaac had stayed. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 13:18","book":"Gen","chapter":13,"verse":18},{"label":"Gn 18:1","book":"Gen","chapter":18,"verse":1},{"label":"Gn 23:19","book":"Gen","chapter":23,"verse":19},{"label":"Jos 14:15","book":"Jos","chapter":14,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Isaac lived 180 years. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gen:35:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He took his last breath and died, and was gathered to his people, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:8","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:17","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 49:33","book":"Gen","chapter":49,"verse":33,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 20:24","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":24,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 20:26","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":26,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 32:50","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":50,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" old and full of days. His sons Esau and Jacob buried him."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 25:8","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":8},{"label":"Gn 25:17","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":17},{"label":"Gn 49:33","book":"Gen","chapter":49,"verse":33},{"label":"Nm 20:24","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":24},{"label":"Nm 20:26","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":26},{"label":"Dt 32:50","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":50}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279310232}